        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/ncv-001",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification via benchmark suite",
        "description": "Solver passes published benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, pipe flow) with L2 norms below 1e-4. Level 2 suffices for MRL 2."
      },
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification was performed against the ASME V&V 20 benchmark suite for incompressible viscous flow. The solver reproduced analytical solutions for fully developed pipe flow and lid-driven cavity flow within L2 norm thresholds of 1e-4, confirming implementation correctness at the level required for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/disc-error-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/disc-error-001",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "GCI < 5% on hemolysis index QoI",
        "description": "Grid convergence index computed on the primary QoI (relative hemolysis index) must be below 5% to demonstrate adequate spatial resolution."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA pump geometry using 4.2M, 10.8M, and 26.5M cell meshes. The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the relative hemolysis index QoI was 2.1% between the medium and fine meshes, satisfying the < 5% acceptance criterion. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-conditions-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
