      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. Key inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are documented and traceable. Sensitivity of the hemolysis index to ±5% variations in inlet flow rate was evaluated informally and found to produce < 8% change in RH, supporting the adequacy of the nominal input specification without requiring a full uncertainty propagation study at this risk level."
    },
    {
